s car-centric vision made room for bicycles only as recreation; and aggressively marginalized, when Ed Koch’s battle against bike messengers culminated in the short-lived 1987 Midtown Bike Ban. On Bicycles illuminates how the city as we know it today—veined with over a thousand miles of bicycle lanes—reflects a fitful journey powered, and opposed, by New York City’s people and its politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aBicycle commutingzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory. 0aBicycle sharing programszNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory. 0aCyclingxGovernment policyzNew York (State)zNew York. 0aCyclingxSocial aspectszNew York (State)zNew York. 0aCyclingzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistory. 0aCyclingzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aUrban transportationzNew York (State)zNew York. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / Middle Atlantic (DC, DE, MD, NJ, NY, PA).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065195908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishz978311061017808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019z9783110606195oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/fris1825640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231544245423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231544245.jpg  a978-3-11-061017-8  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065195-9  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_